('10209762261724645_10209777009733336', 'facebook', '', 'First of all, as a past premium user, I know the promo price is part of the strategy to get more premium users. Giving a gift to strangers, a.k.a. new premium users, is part of the marketing strategy. This also apply to past premium users like me as well.\n\nThe 3 months for a cheaper price (for new premium subscribers) and the 3 months for the price of one month (for some past premium users) is just giving back to customers. I know it\'s unfair for current premium users (paying the regular price or availed the promo price and continues the regular one) for not giving a \"gift\" but it seems understandable because they need to give the royalties back to the artists and/or labels. This is business.\n\nIf you will just threaten them for NOT to give you what you demanded for current premium users, then better CANCEL your subscription and don\'t be stingy! What the hell are you demanding for? Whether you agree for that or not, it doesn\'t matter at all.', '803492005317840896', 'twitter', '', '@IBeMeATRL @Spotify @SpotifyUSA @SpotifyUK @SpotifyCares Why wont you add Thats My Girl by Fifth Harmony to any playlists? Please answer.', 'Spotify', 0.0232141, 0, 0, 1, 2, '2017-02-18 17:07:41', 86, -1, 1, 0.75, 'ot', 'ot'),
