('149147098', 'applestore', 'Fix it!!!!!', 'Ever since ios10, Spotify seems to use double the amount of data and drains my battery amazingly fast. Using it for literally 15 mins brought my battery from 41% to 17 %....', '32440859', 'applestore', 'Update killing my battery', 'I\'ve been using Spotify for years and I\'ve rarely had any complaints about it, but the latest update has given me grief. Sure, I love the UI\'s new look. It\'s very sleek but not too minimalist, and I can ignore the problem of album art not loading because the devs usually fix things like that within a few weeks. But I really can\'t ignore how Spotify is draining my battery rn. My 6s is less than 6 months old, so there\'s no excuse for the app to use 70% of my battery (that\'s literally what it says in the battery usage settings) while it\'s running in the background. I\'m hoping the devs can fix this asap because I can\'t carry a charger with me 24/7.', 'Spotify', 0.280426, 3, 1, 1, 2, '2017-02-21 08:41:46', 177, 2, -1, 0.625, 'ot', 'br'),
