('170387494', 'applestore', 'Developer not responsive', 'There is no way to activate an alert signal that would wake a normal sleeper. IOS Messages provides access to \"minuet\", an IOS sound that is robust and lengthy.  Slack has very short, wimpy sounds and no avenue to connect to the IOS sounds. Slack just cannot be depended upon to alert an average sleeping person.\n\nThe Slack iwatch app has no provision for access to private channels. It is a very overly simplistic attempt so that, yes, we have an app. It is far from functional. \n\nThese deficiencies have been pointed out by many for the past several months. Maybe we will work on that is the response. Obviously they have not.', '811974460488241152', 'twitter', '', 'Sit back and marvel at how incredibly human and good @SlackHQ’s Support team is:\n\nhttps://t.co/j9MIZhRcBy', 'Slack', 0.0374451, 0, 0, 1, 2, '2017-02-21 08:48:05', 189, -2, 1, 0.625, 'ot', 'ot'),
