('193155516', 'applestore', 'Irritating!!!', 'The app started out helpful... but I live in the Stockton to Sierras area and it has taken me to 4 West on a ramp that is closed, of course I reported it. When it redirects me it takes me to the airport and around to where the same ramp is closed.  It also has NO regard for human life and it took me through streets of Stockton where men were walking up to my car and knocking on my windows... The latest trip from Modesto to home it took me on a back road, on and off gravel with seriously 16 turns!! pitch black no cars around. it did deliver me, but the regular route is fine/ no traffic in the boonies. Once it gets you out there you have to follow because you have no freaking idea where you are!!! I can use regular GPS and do as well!', '127967659', 'applestore', 'Go to commute app with caveats', 'It\'s my go to work commute app, but there are definitely some optimizations to be made. Knowing my neighborhood and looking at traffic cams, I\'ll deviate from the recommended route and see my expected arrival go down immediately. \n\nIt often directs me to side streets, but then it causes me to make an impossible left turn across 3 lanes of gridlock so I don\'t think that it accounts for that correctly.\n\nSo not great but the 80% it does do makes me use this often.', 'Waze', 0.221583, 1, 0, 1, 2, '2017-02-21 12:30:30', 215, -1, -1, 1, 'ot', 'ot'),
