('204222119', 'applestore', 'Five star app only worthy of three', 'User friendly explanations on the App Store are not only etiquette but the only acceptable method of informing users of changes and updates.  \n\nI did not purchase the app on your website.  I will certainly not visit your website to learn if the changes.   Put it here like every other developer.  I will them change the rating.', '227775384', 'applestore', 'Update?', 'So what\'s in the update? Why not put it here? A website to see what\'s new? SMH!!', 'Dropbox', 0.201396, 3, 1, 1, 2, '2017-02-21 12:31:22', 219, 1, 1, 1, 'ot', 'ot'),
('20489718', 'applestore', 'Useful but slow', 'The app has become laggy and slow to respond with the iOS 10 update. Frustrating to use and not worth it.', 'gp:AOqpTOGhueQ5eq_pC_kdbX7wdYJ2Nxka6BN65kuYjBzNDYHZlCAGx-1IXI_C7KEUHiHIdTrrNcurQchgXKOosh', 'googleplay', 'Slow', 'Love slack, but the app runs so slow it\'s not usable', 'Slack', 0.419068, 3, 1, 1, 2, '2017-02-21 12:31:49', 220, -1, 0, 0.875, 'br', 'br'),
('206653127', 'applestore', 'Solid app, great communication tool.', 'Use this with the podcasting team for TheNerdParty.com. Way more reliable than tweeting, easier to separate into channels and threads than texting. Sometimes seems to resist using pictures, which can lead to frustrating moments, but really solid and reliable otherwise. Recommend.', '473141349450143_1160373004060304', 'facebook', '', 'Dear Slack, we love you but we need to have one of those chats!!! We have put up with glitches in your iOS and OS apps since you launched, they were at acceptable levels but we expected as you grew and cashed up you would send a little love our way and fix the problems... However over the last few weeks your apps (iOS and OS latest stable versions) are causing us all sorts of grief, badge counts are all over the place, crashing of app multiple times a day (especially on image uploads) and generally driving us crazy with bugs and instability - you are getting to the point you are undateable. As we love you we are willing to give you a chance to fix your problems but you are getting danger zone when we are going to have to consider moving on. You have all the qualities to be everything we need but there are now a number of viable candidates to take your place. Please get your shit together. Lots of love xx', 'Slack', 0.0723456, 0, 0, 1, 2, '2017-02-21 13:27:27', 221, 0, 0, 1, 'ot', 'ot'),
('207484113', 'applestore', 'Great tool .. only one thing missing .. msg unread option', 'We use this tool in a heavily agile environment where all our communication is through slack. We barely use emails. Slack is so much more convenient and it can literally do everything that an email and IM software can do.\nOnly one thing I would suggest to add is the option to mark a msg unread where it will make the channel or name bold until next view.', '501107029', 'applestore', 'Very nice app', 'This is easy to use and very efficient for group messaging. The only problem is a bug that occasionally doesn\'t pick up I have read messages, and it will keep notifying me that I have new messages when they are not new. Other than that this app is great!', 'Slack', 0.15148, 1, 0, 1, 2, '2017-02-21 13:28:07', 222, 2, 2, 1, 'ot', 'br'),
('208029225', 'applestore', 'Live Photos backup ASAP, please!', 'People have been asking for it for over a year.  I was surprised and disappointed this morning when I realized that Dropbox hasn\'t been backing them up.  This is important.  As a Pro user who pays for the Packrat add-on, I have high expectations for app development turnaround time and over a year is too long!', '816157343541067776', 'twitter', '', '@DropboxSupport just giving some feedback on the UX. Most times that I need the list, no wifi or LTE is available. Most stores are blackout', 'Dropbox', 0.0384169, 0, 0, 1, 2, '2017-02-21 13:28:40', 223, 1, 0, 0.875, 'ot', 'ot'),
('209330995', 'applestore', 'Ok for short trips I guess', 'Doesn\'t work for long trips.  I guess they say it overloads their server.   Back to the Mapquest App I guess.', '198788609', 'applestore', 'Great GPS app!!', 'Like graphics, colors, alerts (hazards/police),\nHowever, I find it difficult to stop/cancel program.  Not a straightforward process.  I find I have to hunt for the stop button. Please fix this problem.', 'Waze', 0.0359333, 0, 0, 1, 2, '2017-02-21 13:29:03', 224, 0, 2, 0.75, 'br', 'ot'),
('21104736', 'applestore', 'No GPS lock, directs you to traffic, and dangerous games', 'First, this app has gone haywire on me numerous times in the middle of a route. It just spins around and the car jumps on and off the road you\'re on. It\'s as if it doesn\'t have proper bearing and GPS lock. Restarting the app doesn\'t fix the problem. It\'s a cloud/server issue because when I tried another GPS app, it obtained GPS lock just fine. \n\nSecond, it has also tried to get me to make illegal u-turns, turn the wrong way on one way streets, and in Italy it said I had arrived but I was still a mile away from my destination. When I tried to plug in the address again, it tried to route me 60 miles away! Luckily I knew I was in the right city so i disregarded Waze, and I switched the Apple maps and that got me to the right location.\n\nLastly, Waze comes up with stupid dangerous games and shows advertisements. Recently, I noticed that they had an Easter themed game where you look for Easter eggs on the map.  WTH!  People should be paying attention to the road. Not looking for Easter eggs in a GPS map app.', '86232932633_10154093679587634', 'facebook', '', 'Anyone else having an issue on Android where they app won\'t stay open? I open it and it closes right away. I uninstall, reinstall it and same thing. Memory? More than enough...so it\'s not a resource issue....anyone?', 'Waze', 0.159221, 0, 0, 1, 2, '2017-02-21 13:30:14', 225, 1, 0, 0.875, 'br', 'br'),
