('213341727', 'applestore', 'Rizzzzzle', 'I love this app! It\'s amazing you can find songs that you mainly want to listen too! Only thing is you can\'t find all the songs you preferably want. I have an app that I want to delete with all the songs that I have on it so I can transfer to Spotify but it doesn\'t have all the songs that I seem to be looking for. Overall I\'d give this app a \"4 out of 5 star.\"', 'gp:AOqpTOHDN90MLRjxLK3kTgEZBXamPuxp8ZWC-NVDHQjsn9c8KZTmqlmDCsYBegzu1KLskeIM1SBAZzz3P1Ovsw', 'googleplay', 'Why do we have to pay?', 'I mean it makes sense kinda but why though, I think we should be paying to download the songs not paying to listen to em', 'Spotify', 0.159383, 0, 0, 1, 2, '2017-02-21 13:31:37', 234, 3, 0, 0.625, 'ot', 'ot'),
('215547367', 'applestore', 'U CAN\'T TRUST IT!', 'Will send on long cuts sometimes instead of saving U time. If your not paying attention it sent me in the opposite direction of the map! How is that possible. It usually gives you useless info like car on shoulder ahead and it\'s on the opposite side of the road, I\'m sure it will get better but for now use your brains, this is not a no brainer app!', '86232932633_10154126784452634', 'facebook', '', 'FEATURE REQUEST:   Some sort of detour is delayed setting, where it wouldn\'t deviate from the (normally) fastest route unless the new route was going to save you X minutes.\n-\nlast night I left work in the heavy rain, and I used Waze to get around some traffic issues in the Boston area.  Fine. I got on the the normal highway route, glanced at the phone and had me on there the entire way down.  At some point, I noticed that it had me get off early (I don\'t use the sound as I normally listen to the car\'s radio).  So I followed Waze through some un-known streets, neighborhoods, etc.. And eventually got home.   \nWhat I DON\'T know is how much time I theoretically saved.  If it saved me 30 minutes because of a major accident;  Great!   If Waze thought it was saving me 5 minutes; I\'d rather sit on the highway.  \n-\nIf I could set it to not deviate from norm unless it was saving me 10 or X minutes, that\'d be fantastic....', 'Waze', 0.221931, 0, 0, 1, 2, '2017-02-21 13:32:48', 235, -2, 1, 0.625, 'ot', 'ot');
