('gp:AOqpTOEVFIVpWLyTaAb744Rcxtpro_OgXXgwRNTeTfkMhcJ8idbFPogqUA_zm1MVpR7D0cPVUr3VXXGq6ECEuA', 'googleplay', 'Cracking app to be fair.', 'Used it for quite some time now.  Started a couple of play lists.  Enjoying the choice of music and the quality of streaming too... It would be 5 star, but there is one thing that disappoints me- the shuffle feature.  Sometimes when I pause music or change a song or add to up next it restarts the selection and begins to replay some of the music already played. If that could be remedied, it\'ll be a 5.', '555000518029471_567613026768220', 'facebook', '', 'Thanks.  An update to the community post at https://community.spotify.com/t5/Live-Ideas/Increase-maximum-songs-allowed-in-quot-Your-Music-quot/idc-p/1512340 would be welcome, provided it wasn\'t the same condescending message that has been posted before (which comes across as basically \"suck it\" to the users in that top 1% group - a figure that many in the thread have questioned as not being a real figure).  The idea that increasing the limit so 100% of customers have an awesome experience would result in an \"OK\" experience for 99% of users is felt by many (myself included) to be either absurd logic, or an indication of poor database design on Spotify\'s part - and to tell those of us who pay for Premium \"well, too bad\" is not really an acceptable answer.  There are no good tools to even look and see what is in our saved lists that we might get rid of, so putting it on the customer to figure it out isn\'t generating any good will for Spotify.  You gave us fantastic tools to discover and save new music, and now if we discover and like too much, we\'re penalized.\n\nI understand those who man the SpotifyCares account here aren\'t the decision makers here - but there is a LOT of frustration over the answers we have received to date - as I mentioned a couple messages back, this has been outstanding for two years now, and Spotify has lost many paying customers as a result (many of them have commented in the thread that they\'re dumping Spotify over this limit and moving to other services that do not have this limitation).', 'Spotify', 0.227123, 0, 0, 1, 2, '2017-02-22 14:11:57', 750, 1, 0, 0.875, 'ot', 'ot'),
